# Client build before ship

After changing **Next.js API routes**, **`client/lib/*` helpers**, or **TypeScript types/unions** used by the app:

1. Run **`cd client && npm run build`** and confirm **exit 0** (includes Next typecheck).
2. Do **not** commit or push until the build passes locally.

## TypeScript (`strict: false`)

The client does not use full strict mode. Do not rely on `if (!result.ok)` alone to narrow discriminated unions.

- Use **explicit type guards** (e.g. `isQuotaCheckFailure(x)`) before accessing `.response` or other failure-only fields.
- When adding `Success | Failure` unions in `client/lib`, export guards and use them in all consuming routes.

## Scope

Applies especially to: `client/lib/ai-quota.ts`, `client/app/api/ai/**`, and any shared lib imported by API routes.

Master or user requested **push** does not skip this step when the diff touches the paths above.
